<body>
    <h1>Melt Filtration and Vacuum Degassing in Polymer Recycling Lines</h1>
    <p><strong>Author: Ihor Kryazhev, Process Consultant</strong></p>
    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>Secondary raw materials contain contaminants like sand and moisture. Filtration removes solids, while vacuum degassing eliminates water and odors.</p>
    <h2>2. Melt Filtration</h2>
    <p>Standard for LLDPE recycling: 150-micron screen size. Switching pressure: 120 bar.</p>
    <h2>3. Vacuum Degassing</h2>
    <p>Target vacuum pressure: 50 mbar. A gas condenser is mandatory to protect the vacuum pump.</p>
</body>
